<p>
Let \(V\) be a vector space.
A <b>basis</b> for \(V\) is a subset \(X\) of \(V\)
such that:
<ul>
<li>
\(X\) is
<a knowl="defs/vec/indep">linearly independent</a>
and
</li>
<li>
\(\Span(X) = V\).
</li>
</ul>
</p>
<p>
Related: <a knowl="facts/vec/basis">facts about bases</a>.
</p>
</body>
